  m_Name: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D4_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D4_R
  partName: Pes Proximal Phalanx D4 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right proximal phalanx of the fourth hind digit forms the initial phalangeal
    segment connecting the fourth metatarsal to the middle phalanx. This structure
    contributes to flexibility, digital stability, and proper hindpaw alignment during
    locomotion. Tendons and ligaments associated with the bone control toe movement
    while supporting traction
  - and coordinated paw placement. The fourth digit assists with maintaining balance
    and distributing forces generated during walking, running, and jumping activities.
    Healthy structural alignment is essential for efficient hindlimb movement and
    stable gait mechanics.
